                    <h2>Hoi An opens the 3rd handicraft market night</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="noidung">
                    <p>The new night market is located right next to Hoi An market, operating from 6pm to 11pm every night, selling typical souvenirs of the old town.<br>

                        The new night market opened on March 8, located on 4 streets of Tran Quy Cap, Bach Dang, Tieu La and Hoang Van Thu. The market is expected to be arranged with nearly 100 lots for 47 business households.</p>
                    <img src="https://vcdn1-dulich.vnecdn.net/2019/07/14/8-1563078544.jpg?w=1200&h=0&q=100&dpr=1&fit=crop&s=Bl1tPDscA7h1MnqCe727pQ" height="500px" width="70%"/>
                    <p>Initially, the market had 56 consignments located on Tran Quy Cap street (120 m) and Bach Dang street (43 m), the section below the junction adjoining Hoang Van Thu street 10 m to Tran Quy Cap street. In the near future, the night market will expand to about 40 more lots on Tieu La road (130m long).</p>
                    <img src="https://cdnmedia.thethaovanhoa.vn/Upload/tyTrfgkgEUQwPYuvZ4Kn1g/files/2019/07/1607/hoi-an.jpg" width="70%" height="500px"/>
                    <p>This market will focus on handicraft products, operating from 6pm to 11pm daily.<br>

                        According to the Management Board, the night market is arranged for households that have been doing business in the old town for a long time, which has been cleared and relocated to implement the scheme of arranging street vendors and arranging the sidewalks of Hoi An ancient town. An. With the second night market, Hoi An city wants to stretch visitors from the west to the east of the old town.<br>

                        Previously, in Hoi An old town, there was Nguyen Hoang night market, opposite the Covered Bridge, specializing in selling souvenirs, mainly lanterns; Cong Nu Ngoc Hoa night market, along Hoai River, specializes in cuisine.</p>
